'''Yuji Kaida ([[Wikipedia:Japanese language|Japanese]]: 開田 裕治)''' is a Japanese artist. For [[Tokyopop's Star Wars Manga|Tokyopop's]] ''[[Star Wars Manga: Silver]],'' he created a fold-out color artwork of [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] with an unfinished [[DS-2 Death Star II Mobile Battle Station|Death Star]] in the background.<ref name="SWArchive">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/comics/news20051222.html|text=Inside Tokyopop's ''Star Wars Manga''}}</ref>

Kaida is best known for illustrations of Godzilla and other [[wikipedia:kaiju|kaiju]], earning him the nickname "怪獣絵師" (kaiju eshi, or the Kaiju Painter).<ref name="sankei">{{WebCite|url=https://www.sankei.com/article/20130406-WODJARRSFRNFVOJV6MZ3XAB7FU|text=【装丁魂】『怪獣文藝』装丁＝坂野公一　装画＝開田裕治　東雅夫編|date=2013-04-06|language=Japanese|archivedate=20240112175544}}</ref> He won the 1997 [[wikipedia:Seiun Award|Seiun Award]] for Best Artist.<ref name="Seiun">{{WebCite|url=https://www.sf-fan.gr.jp/awards/list.html|text=Seiun Award List|archivedate=20240111011923|language=Japanese}}</ref>

